The excited surface currents at 8.75, 13.10, and 16.85 GHz when the surface is excited by normal incidence of x- and y-polarized electric fields are shown in Fig. 6c. It can be seen how each part of the scatterer plays a role at different frequencies to realize the required (2i+1)π/2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
